TITLE: Defining API Endpoint with oRPC in TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to define an API endpoint using oRPC. It showcases various features like middleware usage, input validation, error handling, and compatibility with server actions and regular function calls.
SOURCE: https://github.com/unnoq/orpc/blob/main/apps/content/blog/v1-announcement.md#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
const getting = os
  .use(dbProvider)
  .use(requiredAuth)
  .use(rateLimit)
  .use(analytics)
  .use(sentryMonitoring)
  .use(retry({ times: 3 }))
  .route({ method: 'GET', path: '/getting/{id}' })
  .input(z.object({ id: z.string() }))
  .use(canGetting, input => input.id)
  .errors({
    SOME_TYPE_SAFE_ERROR: {
      data: z.object({ something: z.string() })
    }
  })
  .handler(async ({ input, errors, context }) => {
    // do something
  })
  .actionable() // server action compatible
  .callable() // regular function compatible
```

