TITLE: Sending Form Data with Bracket Notation (Bash)
DESCRIPTION: This example shows how to use Bracket Notation in form data sent via a POST request. It demonstrates sending structured data as individual form fields.
SOURCE: https://github.com/unnoq/orpc/blob/main/apps/content/docs/openapi/bracket-notation.md#2025-04-21_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: bash
CODE:
```
curl -X POST http://example.com/api/example \
  -F 'name[first]=John' \
  -F 'name[last]=Doe'
```

